## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID (resolved through the list endpoint; there is no GET-single for rules). |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name. Rule names are **not unique** server-side, so this errors if more than one (or zero) rule matches. Use `id` for a guaranteed unique lookup. |

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | Rule integer ID. |
| `position` | 1-based evaluation position (lower runs first). |
| `name` | Rule name. |
| `comment` | Free-form comment. |
| `action` | Rule action: `accept` or `deny`. |
| `session_types` | Set of session types (empty = Any): `shell`, `graphical`. |
| `resource_types` | Set of inventory resource types (empty = Any); see the table below. |
| `location_ids` | Set of location IDs (empty = Any). |
| `tag_ids` | Set of tag IDs (empty = Any). |
| `role_ids` | Set of role IDs (empty = Any). |
| `command_acl_ids` | Set of command ACL IDs (empty = Any). |
| `notify` | Whether to notify on match. |
| `log` | Whether to log on match. |
| `enabled` | Whether the rule is enabled. |
| `hit_count` | Runtime counter (number of matches). |
| `last_hit_at` | Timestamp of the last match. |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp. |

### `action` values

| action | meaning |
|---|---|
| `accept` | Allow the matched session/command. |
| `deny` | Block the matched session/command. |

### `session_types` values

| session_type | meaning |
|---|---|
| `shell` | Shell (terminal) sessions. |
| `graphical` | Graphical (RDP/VNC-style) sessions. |

